            <!-- Research & Analysis -->
            <section class="project-section">
                <h2 class="project-section-title">Research & Analysis</h2>
                <div class="project-research-block">
                    <h4 class="project-block-title">User Interviews & Qualitative Research</h4>
                    <p class="project-block-text">Conducted interviews with users who had used health and sleep product marketplaces. Key themes included confusion around product claims, desire for personalized suggestions, and need for simple onboarding.</p>
                    <div class="project-highlight-box">
                        <p>"Users wanted to feel understood before being shown productsâ€”conversation first, then discovery."</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="project-research-block">
                    <h4 class="project-block-title">Competitive Analysis & Market Research</h4>
                    <p class="project-block-text">Analyzed competitorsâ€™ chatbot and discovery flows. Identified gaps in sleep-specific guidance and opportunities to differentiate through trust and relevance.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="project-research-block">
                    <h4 class="project-block-title">Problem/User Story Mapping</h4>
                    <p class="project-block-text">Mapped user stories to pain points and opportunities.</p>
                    <ul class="project-bullet-list">
                        <li><strong>What I noticed:</strong> Users often abandoned flows when asked too many questions upfront.</li>
                        <li><strong>What I learned:</strong> Progressive disclosure and optional depth worked better than long forms.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="project-research-block">
                    <h4 class="project-block-title">User Flow / Task Flows</h4>
                    <p class="project-block-text">Defined flows for conversation entry, sleep goal capture, and product discovery.</p>
                    <ul class="project-bullet-list">
                        <li><strong>Goals to accomplish:</strong> Minimal steps to first value; clear path from chat to product detail and checkout.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="project-research-block">
                    <h4 class="project-block-title">Information Architecture / Sitemap</h4>
                    <p class="project-block-text">Structured content and features for the chatbot and linked product experience.</p>
                    <ul class="project-bullet-list">
                        <li><strong>What's included:</strong> Chat home, sleep assessment, recommendations, collections, and account settings.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="project-research-block">
                    <h4 class="project-block-title">Key Learnings from Research</h4>
                    <p class="project-block-text">Trust and relevance were the main drivers. Users responded well to conversational interfaces when they felt the system understood their context.</p>
                    <div class="project-highlight-box">
                        <p>Key finding: Combining AI conversation with curated product collections led to higher engagement and completion rates in testing.</p>
                    </div>
